com.vectorprint.configuration.decoration.visiting

Interface DecoratorVisitor<E extends EnhancedMap>

  • Type Parameters:
    E -
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ObservableVisitor, ParsingVisitor, PreparingVisitor

    public interface DecoratorVisitor<E extends EnhancedMap>
    You can define a visitor that allows you to access a certain type of EnhancedMap in the stack and call its methods. This way you can for example add properties from a url or add observables after the stack of properties is defined.
    Author:
    Eduard Drenth at VectorPrint.nl
    See Also:
    AbstractPropertiesDecorator.accept(com.vectorprint.configuration.decoration.visiting.DecoratorVisitor), SettingsField, SettingsAnnotationProcessor
